# CODEOWNERS Template
#
# Copy this file to .github/CODEOWNERS in your repository.
# Remove this header comment block after customizing.
#
# CODEOWNERS defines who is automatically requested for review when a PR
# touches a matching path. Combined with branch protection requiring code
# owner review, this ensures governance-sensitive changes always reach the
# right reviewers — regardless of who opens the PR (including agents).
#
# Syntax:
#   <path-pattern>    @owner1 @owner2
#   <path-pattern>    @org/team-name
#
# Rules:
# - Patterns are matched from bottom to top. The last matching rule wins.
# - Teams are specified as @org/team-name.
# - Multiple owners mean ALL owners are requested for review.
# - The first line sets the global default for any path not matched below.
#
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ---
# Global default
# All files not matched by a more specific rule below are owned by the
# framework maintainers team. Replace with your organization's team.
# ---
*                                           @your-org/framework-maintainers

# ---
# Framework Core — Governance and Schemas
# Changes to the governance registry or schemas affect all governed activities
# across every team using this framework. Require 2 designated owners.
# Pair with branch protection: "require_code_owner_review: true" and
# "required_approving_review_count: 2" for these paths via CODEOWNERS routing.
# ---
/config/governance-registry.yaml            @your-org/framework-maintainers @your-org/security-leads
/config/aispec.config.example.yaml          @your-org/framework-maintainers
/framework/schemas/                         @your-org/framework-maintainers @your-org/security-leads

# ---
# Documentation
# Docs owners review all documentation changes. Technical writers or
# designated docs maintainers should own this path.
# ---
/docs/                                      @your-org/docs-maintainers
/README.md                                  @your-org/docs-maintainers @your-org/framework-maintainers
/CONTRIBUTING.md                            @your-org/framework-maintainers

# ---
# SDLC Standards
# Changes to SDLC standards docs affect all adopting teams. Require
# framework maintainer review.
# ---
/docs/sdlc/                                 @your-org/framework-maintainers

# ---
# CI/CD — GitHub Actions Workflows
# Workflow changes can affect security posture (e.g., adding write permissions,
# changing secret usage, bypassing required checks). Route to security leads
# and framework maintainers.
# ---
/.github/workflows/                         @your-org/framework-maintainers @your-org/security-leads
/.github/CODEOWNERS                         @your-org/framework-maintainers

# ---
# Agent Definitions
# Changes to agent definitions affect governed behavior. Route to the
# framework maintainers who own the governance registry.
# ---
/.github/agents/                            @your-org/framework-maintainers
/Skills/                                    @your-org/framework-maintainers

# ---
# Playbooks
# Adoption playbooks guide teams through onboarding. Changes should be
# reviewed by someone who has validated the playbook against real repositories.
# ---
/docs/playbooks/                            @your-org/framework-maintainers @your-org/docs-maintainers

# ---
# Website
# Website source is owned by the docs/web team.
# ---
/website/                                   @your-org/docs-maintainers

# ---
# Tests
# Test changes are owned by the framework maintainers team.
# Test coverage reductions require explicit justification in the PR.
# ---
/tests/                                     @your-org/framework-maintainers
